Hello ! I’m **Angélique Porciani**, a biostatistician and data scientist with over 12 years of experience working with complex data in life sciences.

Over the years, I’ve developed strong expertise in statistical modelling and data analysis with R applied to biological systems, through a wide range of projects in epidemiology, health, and vector ecology.

I particularly enjoy working with complex, time-dependent data, such as time series and longitudinal datasets, applying statistical and machine learning methods to tackle diverse analytical challenges. I also have experience with survival and dose-response models to assess the efficacy of new molecules in epidemiological studies.

Looking forward, I am eager to apply machine learning approaches to high-dimensional and genetic datasets, including variable selection and exploration of complex biological patterns.

What really motivates me is making sense of complex, real-world data and turning it into meaningful and actionable insights.

Beyond the technical side, I’ve coordinated projects, supervised students, and shared knowledge through teaching, publications, and conferences. I value collaboration and enjoy working in interdisciplinary environments.

I’m currently seeking opportunities in applied research settings such as CROs, biotech companies, or SMEs, where I can contribute to projects involving complex data and meaningful scientific questions in life sciences.
